{"lemma":"فِتْرُ","slug":"فِتْرُ","root":"ف.ت.ر","root_slug":"ف-ت-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ت-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32908","n32912","n32913","n32914","n32916"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%90%D8%AA%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32908","headword_ar":"فَتَرَ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwrN","text_ar":"فُتُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futaArN","text_ar":"فُتَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the latter is thus accord. to the M, and some copies of the K, and in the TA is said to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"guraAbN","text_ar":"غُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in the CK and one MS. copy of the K I find it written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitaAr","text_ar":"فِتَار"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing, M, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became allayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still, after vehemence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became gentle after violence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatara","text_ar":"فَتَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano Eamalihi","text_ar":"عَنْ عَمَلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,) aro."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwrN","text_ar":"فُتُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remitted, flagged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became remiss,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid, in his work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he remitted therein after vigour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemence; became gentle therein after violence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b3-  Hence, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatara AlHar~u","text_ar":"فَتَرَ الحَرُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatorapN","text_ar":"فَتْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwrN","text_ar":"فُتُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The heat remitted after vehemence; became gentle after violence:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heat remitted, abated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flagged; became languid and faint:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the verb is used in like manner of other things; (S;) for instance, of a price: (Fr, in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qT","text_ar":"قط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and of a man, signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid, languid and faint,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lax in the joints;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 799;) [as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tft~r","text_ar":"تفتّر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xtr","text_ar":"ختر"},{"kind":"text","text":", &c.]. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatara Albarodu","text_ar":"فَتَرَ البَرْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cold abated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remitted;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became allayed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatara AlmaA='u","text_ar":"فَتَرَ المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water abated in heat so as to become tepid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lukewarm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between hot and cold;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtirN","text_ar":"فَاتِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the water ceased to be hot."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatara jisomuhu","text_ar":"فَتَرَ جِسْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"futuwrN","text_ar":"فُتُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His body became"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lax in the joints, and weak."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatara AlT~arofu","text_ar":"فَتَرَ الطَّرْفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The look of the eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyes, became languishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languid;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ainokasara naZaruhu","text_ar":"اِنْكَسَرَ نَظَرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IKtt, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarofN faAtirN","text_ar":"طَرْفٌ فَاتِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below; and see also 4.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatarahu","text_ar":"فَتَرَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He measured it by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitor","text_ar":"فِتْر"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, O, K:) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abarahu","text_ar":"شَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he measured it by the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibor","text_ar":"شِبْر"},{"kind":"text","text":". ” (M, O.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","S","O","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n32912","headword_ar":"فُتْرٌ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nabiy~ap","text_ar":"نَبِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suforap","text_ar":"سُفْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of palm-leaves, upon which flour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"meal, is sifted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-' Abbád, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":["O"]},{"entry_id":"n32913","headword_ar":"فِتْرٌ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space between the extremity of the thumb and that of the fore finger"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they are stretched out asunder"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the usual manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for measuring"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afotaArN","text_ar":"اَفْتَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n32914","headword_ar":"فَتَرٌ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatorapN","text_ar":"فَتْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfataru","text_ar":"الفَتَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. in the K as signifyfying “ the muscles, ” and also as signifying “ a certain well-known measure, or quantity, of wheat, ” is a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfaA^oru","text_ar":"الفَاْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned in both of these senses in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fA^r","text_ar":"فار"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the TS [and in the O]. (TA. [See art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fA^r","text_ar":"فار"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n32916","headword_ar":"فِتَرٌّ","root":"ftr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fatorapN","text_ar":"فَتْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain fish,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"speckled, and having upon it a blackness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that when a man treads upon it, he is affected with a languor"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tremour"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his legs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he becomes drowned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus described by Ibn-' Abbád, (O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he sweats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(thus in copies of the K:) it is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raE~aAdap","text_ar":"رَعَّادَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"torpedo"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"found in the Nile of Egypt."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","K"]}]}}